-- South Korea’s Household Bank Loans Rise to 453.6 Trillion Won
-- B y   E u n k y u n g   S e o
-- 2012-05-09T03:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-09/south-korea-s-household-bank-loans-rise-to-453-6-trillion-won.html
South Korea ’s bank lending to
households rose by 1.3 trillion won ($1.1 billion) last month to
453.6 trillion won, the highest since December, as people
borrowed to buy homes.  Mortgage lending rose 1 trillion won to 308 trillion won,
today’s e-mailed statement from the  Bank of Korea  showed. Loans
to companies gained 6.3 trillion won to 577.6 trillion won.  The broadest measure of  money supply , M2, was unchanged in
March from the previous month after a 0.7 percent gain in
February, according to a separate central bank statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
